{"TopicDetails": {"type": 0, "ccm2Id": 44881246, "cftId": 0, "identifier": "EP-LINC-SUBV-2022-CONF-INT-01", "title": "Support for training interpreting 2022-2023 organisation of Master or post-graduate courses", "publicationDateLong": 1648684800000, "callIdentifier": "EP-LINC-SUBV-2022-CONF-INT", "callTitle": "Support for training interpreting 2022-2023", "callccm2Id": 44881262, "allowPartnerSearch": true, "frameworkProgramme": {"id": 43697167, "abbreviation": "EP", "description": "European Parliament"}, "programmeDivision": [{"id": 43697187, "abbreviation": "EP-1-1", "description": "Grants in the Area of Communication"}], "topicMGAs": [], "sme": false, "actions": [{"status": {"id": 31094503, "abbreviation": "Closed", "description": "Closed"}, "types": [{"typeOfAction": "EP-PJG EP Project Grants", "typeOfMGA": [{"id": 43694065, "abbreviation": "EP-AG", "description": "EP Action Grant Budget-Based"}]}], "plannedOpeningDate": "31 March 2022", "submissionProcedure": {"id": 31094504, "abbreviation": "single-stage", "description": "single-stage"}, "deadlineDates": ["11 May 2022"]}], "latestInfos": [], "budgetOverviewJSONItem": {"budgetTopicActionMap": {"3380260": [{"action": "EP-LINC-SUBV-2022-CONF-INT-01 - EP-PJG EP Project Grants", "plannedOpeningDate": "31 March 2022", "deadlineModel": "single-stage", "deadlineDates": ["11 May 2022"], "budgetYearMap": {"2022": 400000}, "budgetTopicActionMap": {}}], "3380262": [{"action": "EP-LINC-SUBV-2022-CONF-INT-02 - EP-PJG EP Project Grants", "plannedOpeningDate": "31 March 2022", "deadlineModel": "single-stage", "deadlineDates": ["11 May 2022"], "budgetYearMap": {"2022": 100000}, "budgetTopicActionMap": {}}]}, "budgetYearsColumns": ["2022"]}, "description": "<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">ExpectedOutcome</SPAN>:<p>To ensure the availability of a sufficient number of qualified conference interpreters, Directorate-General for Logistics and Interpretation for Conferences supports and assists in strengthening training programmes by providing professional and financial assistance. The aim of these activities is to help produce new generations of qualified conference interpreters who may, subsequently, be recruited by the EU institutions, and in particular by the European Parliament, as officials or as accredited conference interpreting agents.</p>\n<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">Objective</SPAN>:<p>As a provider of interpretation services in the European Parliament, and increasingly to other EU institutions and bodies, the mission of the Directorate-General for Logistics and Interpretation for Conferences is to ensure that a sufficient number of qualified conference interpreters are available to enable the EU institutions and bodies to function properly in a context of linguistic diversity including at regular events, all over the world, where wide language cover is required.</p><p>Under the principle of subsidiarity, Member States have the obligation to provide the necessary training. The European Parliament identifies the language combinations and skills that best match its needs, and assists universities in training high quality conference interpreters within these priority combinations.</p><p>The programme contributes to this mission by supporting the following actions in the field of interpretation:</p><ul level=\"0\"><li>The promotion of quality and linguistic diversity in the teaching of conference interpreting in the official languages of the EU, of the candidate countries, and of the countries which are the main political partners of the Union;</li><li>The establishment of postgraduate centres of excellence;</li><li>Cooperation among postgraduate courses from different European, candidate and third countries offering relevant language combinations;</li><li>Regional cooperation among universities with complementary language regimes;</li> </ul>\n<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">Scope</SPAN>:<ul level=\"0\"><li>Higher Education Institutions, Universities, university institutes, consortia and associations of universities or institutes, which offer or coordinate postgraduate courses specialising in conference interpreting.</li><li>Associations, consortia and bodies, whose main mission is to support cooperation and disseminate best practices in the field of worldwide conference interpreter training.</li> </ul>\n", "conditions": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;color:#404040;&#10;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">Conditions</span></b><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;color:#404040;&#10;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n<p><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color:#404040;mso-themecolor:&#10;text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">1.&nbsp;</span></b><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">Admissibility conditions: </span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">described in section 4 of the<a href=\"https://www.europarl.europa.eu/contracts-and-grants/files/grants/interpretation-for-conferences/2-call-for-proposals-2022-2023.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"> call document</a></span>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">Proposal page limits and layout:</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:&#10;EN-US\"> described in Part B of the Application Form available in the Submission System<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">2. Eligible countries: </span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">described in section 5 of the <a href=\"https://www.europarl.europa.eu/contracts-and-grants/files/grants/interpretation-for-conferences/2-call-for-proposals-2022-2023.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">call document</a><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">3. Other eligibility conditions:</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\"> describ